You won't need lunch :) No free wifi (or free internet at all) is the only negative.	What I did not like at all was the lack of free internet, still many hotels are requesting payment, and Una Rome is one of them.	PS if you do decide to stay here despite the reviews, use the special offer on TripAdvisor for free internet access, otherwise it is around €25 per 24 hours.	I did not like the idea of having to pay for internet connection in the hotel.	We did pay 3E for 30 minutes of wifi, but did not consider it an issue.